A 47-YEAR-OLD suspect appeared in the Amanzimtoti Magistrate s Court and charged with possession of suspected stolen property on 2 May. The accused was found in possession of items valued at R50 000, including laptops, chargers, passports, driver s licences, identity books, bank cards, business cards, binoculars, GPS s, cameras and camera bags, image stabilisers, camera lens and cover, camera batteries and charger and a charging cord, a remote jammer, keys, glasses and several phones.The case has been postponed pending a formal bail application on 9 May. - Supplied. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.